data.title: Wilhelm Ferdinand “Wutz” Galland (1914
data.meta_description: Major (Majoor) Todes-/Vermisstenort: Hees Lüttich (Luik)   Wutz Galland, born 23-10-1914 in Bochum, was one of four Galland brothers to serve in the Luftwaffe. The oldest brother Fritz Galland served in a fighter and reconnaissance unit and survived the war. His older brother, Lieutenant General der Flieger, Adolf...
